<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-14618 AND RTLO-16618
        SERIES - INSTALL - SHIFTER HOUSING
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>SHIFTER HOUSING</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place all three mainshaft sliding clutches in the neutral position (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13019t0">Figure 290</hotlnk>). Install shifter housing gasket in position.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13019t0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13019t0" filename="../figg13/G13019t0.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 290. Place Mainshaft Sliding Clutches in Neutral Position</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With all three shift yokes in the neutral position, install the shifter housing assembly on
                the case, fitting the shift yokes into the slots of the corresponding sliding clutches (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13019t1">Figure 291</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13019t1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13019t1" filename="../figg13/G13019t1.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 291. Install Shifter Housing Assembly on Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Loctite 242 or equivalent to the bolt threads. Install the bolts in shifter housing
                and tighten to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#183;m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13019t2">Figure 292</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13019t2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13019t2" filename="../figg13/G13019t2.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 292. Install Bolts in Shifter Housing and Tighten</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>There are two sizes of bolts. The 1 1/2 inch bolts are used with lifting eyes.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
